definition.value: A fatty acid ester formed between oleic acid and all-trans-retinol.
A fatty acid ester formed between stearic acid and all-trans-retinol.
A fatty acid ester formed between linoleic acid and all-trans-retinol.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of tritrans,heptacis-undecaprenyl phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An undecaprenyl phosphate having three (E)- and seven (Z)-double bonds.
A UDP-N-acetyl-D-muramate in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A dicarboxylic acid that is suberic acid substituted at position 3 by a hydroxy group.
A 2-hydroxydicarboxylic acid that is the 2-hydroxy derivative of suberic acid.
UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-gamma-D-glutamyl-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alaninate(3-) in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A hydroxytryptophan that is tryptophan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2 on the indole ring.
Any protein kinase inhibitor that inhibits the action of an Aurora kinase (a group of serine/threonine kinases that are essential for cell proliferation).
A cationic sphingoid that is the conjugate acid of 15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine, obtained by protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxytryptophan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4 on the indole ring.

A benzazepine that is 2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1H-2-benzazepine which is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 8 and on the nitrogen atom by a 2-(p-chlorophenyl)ethylaminothiocarbonyl group. A synthetic analogue of capsaicin, it was the first reported capsaicin receptor antagonist.
Any substance which blocks the painful sensation of heat caused by capsaicin acting on the TRPV1 ion channel.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as 15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine.
A sphingomyelin in which the sphingoid component is specified as 4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine.
A hydroxytryptophan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7 on the indole ring.

A monocarboxylic acid that is 2-(phenylsulfanyl)isobutyric acid in which the phenyl group is substituted at the para- position by a 3-aza-7-cyclohexylhept-1-yl group in which the nitrogen is acylated by a (cyclohexylamino)carbonyl group.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 1-deoxy-11beta-hydroxypentalenic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 5-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 1-deoxy-11-oxopentalenic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Any compound which acts on the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor.
A PPAR modulator which activates the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-alpha.
A CDP-4-dehydro-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose(2-) in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A CDP-D-abequose(2-) in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A CDP-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose(2-) in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A triterpene that is docosa-2,6,11,16,20-pentaene bearing six methyl substituents at positions 2, 6, 10, 13, 17 and 21 as well as a vinyl substituent at position 10 (with all-E-configuration).
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentalenolactone D, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentalenolactone E, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentalenolactone F, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pentalenolactone, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cobalt-precorrin-7.
A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cobalt-precorrin-8.
A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cob(II)yrinic acid c monoamide.
A tricyclic sesquiterpenoid that is pentalenene in which the 13-methyl group is oxidsed to the carboxylic acid and a hydroxy substituent is located at position 11.
A tricyclic sesquiterpenoid that is pentalenene in which the 13-methyl group is oxidsed to the carboxylic acid and a keto group is located at position 11.
A sphingoid that is hexadecasphing-4-enine substituted at position 15 by a methyl group.
A CDP-D-abequose in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A CDP-4-dehydro-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
An imidazolyl carboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by an imidazol-1-yl group.
A CDP-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose in which the anomeric centre of the pyranose fragment has alpha-configuration.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is olean-12-ene substituted by carboxy group at position 28 and hydroxy groups at positions 3, 16 and 21 (the 3beta,16alpha,21beta stereoisomer).
A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by an imidazol-5-yl group.
A sesquiterpene lactone obtained by regioselective Bayer-Villiger oxidation of 1-deoxy-11-oxopentalenic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by an imidazol-2-yl group.
A sesquiterpene lactone obtained by formal dehydrogenation of the 4-methyl position of pentalenolactone D.
An imidazolyl carboxylic acid that is lactic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by an imidazol-1-yl group.
A tetracyclic sesquiterpene lactone obtained by formal epoxidation of the 4-methylene group of pentalenolactone E.
A N(2)-acylglutamine that has indol-3-ylacetyl as the acyl group.
